<FIRST>r i PM-ToxicCookies     10-17 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Toxic Cookies,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Factories Ordered Closed After 36 Die from Contaminated Cookies</HEAD>
<UNK>Eds: One name only for Suharto and Sudomo</UNK>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government has ordered the closure
of five factories that produced contaminated cookies that have
killed 36 people since mid-summer, a senior official says.
   Sudomo, the government's coordinator for defense and political
affairs, told reporters Tuesday after meeting with President
Suharto that the government was trying to withdraw all contaminated
cookies from markets throughout the country.
   Kusparmono Irsan, director of the Criminal Investigation
Department, said employees of a freight-forwarding firm confused
sacks of ammonium bicarbonate, an ingredient in baking powder, with
sodium nitrate when unloading cargo from Hong Kong in April.
   The sodium nitrate was sent to the cookie factories by mistake,
and beginning in July ended up in cookies. Sodium nitrate is used
in making explosives and fertilizers.
   The government so far has been unable to determine how many
contaminated cookies were produced.
</TEXT>
