<FIRST>u a AM-PropaneFire     10-17 0131</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Propane Fire,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Propane Truck Accident Sets Homes on Fire, Forces Evacuation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MASSIEVILLE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An accident involving a tanker truck
carrying propane gas set at least two mobile homes on fire late
Monday night and forced the evacuation of a trailer park, a
sheriff's official said.
   ``There's two or three residences on fire,'' said Ross County
sheriff's Sgt. Don Haber. There were no immediate reports of
injuries, he said.
   It was not known how many vehicles were involved in the 11:10
p.m. accident, Haber said. ``The tanker overturned or exploded.
We're not sure,'' the sergeant said.
   Authorities ordered the evacuation of Charm's Trailer Park about
two miles from this village some 50 miles south of Columbus. Haber
did not know how many people were forced from their homes.
</TEXT>
