<HEAD>International Press Institute Condemns Newspaper Murders</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Colombia, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leaders of the International Press Institute have
called on the president of Colombia to guarantee the safety of
co-workers of two murdered newspaper employees.
   ``The International Press Institute is deeply distressed by the
callous murder last Tuesday of Martha Luz Lopez, El Espectador's
local advertising manager, and Miguel Soler, the newspaper's
circulation manager,'' the officials wrote in a letter to Colombian
President Virgilio Barco Vargas.
