Colombia and calls upon your government to guarantee the protection
of El Espectador's staff and property. Many of our brave colleagues
have given their lives in the cause of freedom and also in the
exposure of the drug racketeers in Colombia. We urge you to ensure
that their sacrifice has not been in vain.''
   The letter was signed by Enrique Zileri of Lima, Peru, the
chairman of the IPI, and by Peter Galliner, the institute's
director.
