<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Typhoons,0114</SECOND>
<HEAD>Typhoons Kill 63</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three typhoons that hit southern China's Hainan
Island during the first two weeks of October killed 63 people, an
official report said Tuesday.
   Fifteen other people are missing and feared dead, and 712 are
injured, the Xinhua News Agency said.
   Telephone lines, roads, rices paddies and rubber plantations on
the tropical island south of Hong Kong also were heavily damaged,
it said, but gave no figure for the economic losses.
   The worst storm was Typhoon Brian, which hit Oct. 2 and killed
40 people. Two others had followed by Oct. 13.
   Xinhua said the public has donated $658,000 toward relief work.
