<FIRST>r i AM-Netherlands-Explosion     10-17 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Netherlands-Explosion,0129</SECOND>
<HEAD>Storage Tanks With Toxic Chemicals Explodes, Killing Three</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROTTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storage tank containing a toxic
chemical exploded and caught fire Tuesday, killing three
maintenance workers and injuring three, police said.
   The tank of the Paktank company, in Rotterdam's Botlek port
area, exploded at midmorning while the crew was working on it,
according to police spokesman Hans Stoop. He said it took
firefighters four hours to control the blaze.
   The cause of the blast was not immediately known, Stoop said.
   The tank contained 250 tons of acrylonytril, a highly flammable
and toxic chemical used in the plastics industry, the spokesman
said.
   Nearby residents were advised to keep their windows closed for
several hours, but no evacuations were necessary, Stoop said.
</TEXT>
