effort to save the elephant _ just declared an endangered species _
stores have stopped selling ivory, fashionable people no longer
wear it and even Vladimir Horowitz agreed to accept something other
than ivory keys next time he orders a Steinway piano.
   Jewelry made from the tusks of elephants became unpopular so
fast that some observers see the trend as evidence that a new
environmental ethic is taking hold among fashion-setters.
