<HEAD>Dollar Locked in Narrow Range; Gold Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar was fluctuating in a narrow range in
European trading today, and was unchanged against the West German
mark.
   Gold was lower in sluggish trading.
   Dealers said calm had returned to the markets following the
uncertainty Monday because of gyrations on the stock exchanges.
   In Tokyo, the dollar closed at 142.25 yen, up 1.50 yen from
Monday's close. Later in London the dollar traded at 142.35 yen.
   In London, the pound fell back to $1.5755, compared to $1.5820
late Monday.
