<HEAD>Posts 18 Percent Jump in Third-Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: fixes million to billion in 3rd graf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp. on Tuesday said its
third-quarter income spurted 18 percent, reflecting greater use of
its local telephone networks and strong growth in its
celluar-telephone operations.
   The company said after-tax earnings in the three months ended
Sept. 30 reached a quarterly record of $368 million, or $1.06 per
share, up from $313 million, or 91 cents a share, a year earlier.
   Revenue rose about 9 percent to $4.4 billion from $4 billion in
the comparable period a year ago.
   ``GTE's record earnings are particularly noteworthy in light of
the regulatory and competitive pressures affecting our
businesses,'' said James L. Johson, chairman and chief executive
officer.
   ``Fueled by increased usage of our local-telephone networks
along with very strong growth in our cellular-telephone operations
and solid performance in our other businesses, the trends in
earnings per share and return on equity continue to be positive,''
he said.
   For the first nine months of this year, GTE earned $1 billion,
about a 14 percent jump from the prior year's $898 million.
Earnings per share were $3.01 vs. $2.62.
   Revenue in the first three quarters of 1989 rose about 5 percent
to $12.8 billion from $12.2 billion.
