   Stocks seesawed to a lower close Tuesday and
airline issues had another rough ride.
   Computer-driven program trades periodically rocked the market,
causing the third straight volatile session on Wall Street. Trading
was heavy but well below Monday's huge volume.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials ended the day down 18.65
points at 2,638.73.
   The drop was partly due to profit-taking. Investors sold to
collect profits amassed during the previous session's blue-chip
rally that helped the Dow Jones industrial average bounce back by
more than 88 points from Friday's 190-point dive.
