<SECOND>AM-Earns-Microsoft,0134</SECOND>
<HEAD>Microsoft Earnings Up 36 Percent in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REDMOND, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 36 percent gain in net income and a 33
percent increase in revenue for the first fiscal quarter were
reported Tuesday by Microsoft Corp., a leading computer software
manufacturer.
   Microsoft said net income for the three months ending Sept. 30
rose to $49.6 million or 87 cents a share, compared with $36.6
million or 65 cents a share in the same period last year.
   Revenues were $235.2 million, compared with $176.4 million for
the first quarter of Microsoft's previous fiscal year, the
statement said.
   The gains reflect higher sales worldwide, greater emphasis on
retail products and increased spending on research and development,
said Frank Gaudette, senior vice president and chief financial
officer.
